      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">People</a> * Michel Van den Bergh</b>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/File:Van_den_bergh_michel_2010.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/18/Van_den_bergh_michel_2010.jpg/330px-Van_den_bergh_michel_2010.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"370\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/18/Van_den_bergh_michel_2010.jpg/500px-Van_den_bergh_michel_2010.jpg 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/1/18/Van_den_bergh_michel_2010.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/File:Van_den_bergh_michel_2010.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Michel Van den Bergh <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></div></div></div> \n<p><b>Michel Van den Bergh</b>,<br />\na Belgian mathematician, Ph.D. in 1985 and <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Habilitation\">Habilitation</a> (Hoger Aggregaat) in 1990 from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/University_of_Antwerp\">University of Antwerp</a>, and director of research at the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Fund_for_Scientific_Research\">Fund for Scientific Research</a>, also affiliated with the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/University_of_Hasselt\">University of Hasselt</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diepenbeek\">Diepenbeek</a>, and the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vrije_Universiteit_Brussel\">Free University of Brussels</a>. He was visiting researcher and professor at  <a href=\"/Massachusetts_Institute_of_Technology\" title=\"Massachusetts Institute of Technology\">MIT</a> in <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cambridge,_Massachusetts\">Cambridge, Massachusetts</a>, the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Louis_Pasteur_University\">Louis Pasteur University</a> in <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Strasbourg\">Strasbourg</a>, the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematical_Sciences_Research_Institute\">Mathematical Sciences Research Institute</a> in <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Berkeley,_California\">Berkeley, California</a>, and the  <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mittag-Leffler_Institute\">Mittag Leffler Institute</a> in <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stockholm\">Stockholm</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>.  His research interests include <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Algebraic_topology\">algebraic topology</a> and <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Algebraic_geometry\">algebraic geometry</a>, in particular <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Noncommutative_algebraic_geometry\">noncommutative algebraic geometry</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Computer_Chess\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Computer Chess</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Selected_Publications\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Selected Publications</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#1980_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">1980 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#1990_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">1990 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#2000_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2000 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#2010_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2010 ...</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Forum_Posts\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Forum Posts</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#2008_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2008 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#2010_..._2\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2010 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-10\"><a href=\"#2015_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2015 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-11\"><a href=\"#2020_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2020 ...</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-12\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-13\"><a href=\"#General\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">General</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-14\"><a href=\"#Computer_Chess_2\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Computer Chess</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-15\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Computer_Chess\">Computer Chess</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Michel_Van_den_Bergh&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Computer Chess\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p>Michel Van den Bergh's professional interests in mathematics is supplemented by chess and computer chess programming. He worked on <a href=\"/Toga\" title=\"Toga\">Toga II</a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/POSIX\">Posix</a> ports, on <a href=\"/index.php?title=Icsdrone&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Icsdrone (page does not exist)\">icsdrone</a>, an interface between an ICS (<a href=\"/Chess_Server\" title=\"Chess Server\">Internet Chess Server</a>) and a chess engine supporting the <a href=\"/Chess_Engine_Communication_Protocol\" title=\"Chess Engine Communication Protocol\">Chess Engine Communication Protocol</a>, and made an attempt to transform <a href=\"/GNU_Chess\" title=\"GNU Chess\">GNU Chess</a> into a modern Chess Engine Communication Protocol compliant engine. He is in the process to improve version 5 with various <a href=\"/Static_Exchange_Evaluation\" title=\"Static Exchange Evaluation\">SEE</a> based <a href=\"/Pruning\" title=\"Pruning\">pruning</a> techniques and optimizations, where SEESign is faster to determine if the SEE value is below some threshold than computing its actual value <sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>, and further applied <a href=\"/Automated_Tuning\" title=\"Automated Tuning\">parameter tuning</a> using <a href=\"/R%C3%A9mi_Coulom\" title=\"Rémi Coulom\">Rémi Coulom's</a> <a href=\"/CLOP\" title=\"CLOP\">CLOP</a>, Confident Local Optimization for Noisy Black-Box Parameter Tuning <sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>. More recently, Michel Van den Bergh is engaged in <a href=\"/Match_Statistics\" title=\"Match Statistics\">match statistics</a> and <a href=\"/Match_Statistics#SPRT\" title=\"Match Statistics\">sequential probability ratio test</a>.\n</p>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Selected_Publications\">Selected Publications</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Michel_Van_den_Bergh&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Selected Publications\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p><sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"1980_...\">1980 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Michel_Van_den_Bergh&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: 1980 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Michel Van den Bergh</a> (<b>1984</b>). <i>A duality theorem for Hopf algebras, Methods in ring theory</i>. (<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Antwerp\">Antwerp</a>, 1983), NATO Advanced Science Institutes Series C: Mathematical and Physical Sciences, Vol. 129, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/D._Reidel\">Reidel</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dordrecht\">Dordrecht</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Michel Van den Bergh</a> (<b>1987</b>). <i>Linearisations of binary and ternary forms</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Journal_of_Algebra\">Journal of Algebra</a>, Vol. 109 </li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Michel Van den Bergh</a> (<b>1989</b>). <i>Trace rings of generic matrices are Cohen-Macaulay</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Journal_of_the_American_Mathematical_Society\">Journal of the American Mathematical Society</a>, Vol. 2, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://hardy.uhasselt.be/personal/vdbergh/Publications/cmtrace.pdf\">pdf</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"1990_...\">1990 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Michel_Van_den_Bergh&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: 1990 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Michel Van den Bergh</a> (<b>1991</b>). <i>Cohen-Macaulayness of modules of covariants</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inventiones_Mathematicae\">Inventiones Mathematicae</a>, Vol. 106, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://hardy.uhasselt.be/personal/vdbergh/Publications/stanley.pdf\">pdf</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Michel Van den Bergh</a> (<b>1991</b>). <i>Explicit rational forms for the Poincar'e series of the trace rings of generic matrices</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Israel_Journal_of_Mathematics\">Israel Journal of Mathematics</a>, Vol. 73</li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Michel Van den Bergh</a> (<b>1993</b>). <i>Cohen-Macaulayness of semi-invariants for tori</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Transactions_of_the_American_Mathematical_Society\">Transactions of the American Mathematical Society</a>, Vol. 336</li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Michel Van den Bergh</a> (<b>1994</b>). <i>A converse to Stanley's conjecture for Sl2</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Proceedings_of_the_American_Mathematical_Society\">Proceedings of the American Mathematical Society</a>, Vol. 121, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://hardy.uhasselt.be/personal/vdbergh/Publications/convst.pdf\">pdf</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2000_...\">2000 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Michel_Van_den_Bergh&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: 2000 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Michel Van den Bergh</a> (<b>2002, 2004</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://arxiv.org/abs/math/0211064\">Non-commutative crepant resolutions</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.amazon.com/The-Legacy-Niels-Henrik-Abel/dp/3540438262\">The Legacy of Niels Hendrik Abel</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Springer_Science%2BBusiness_Media\">Springer</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Michel Van den Bergh</a> (<b>2004</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://projecteuclid.org/DPubS?service=UI&amp;version=1.0&amp;verb=Display&amp;handle=euclid.dmj/1082665284\">Three-dimensional flops and noncommutative rings</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Duke_Mathematical_Journal\">Duke Mathematical Journal</a>, Vol. 122</li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Michel Van den Bergh</a> (<b>2004</b>). <i>A remark on a theorem by Deligne</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Proceedings_of_the_American_Mathematical_Society\">Proceedings of the American Mathematical Society</a>, Vol. 132 <sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Michel Van den Bergh</a> (<b>2005</b>). <i>On the ZD∞ category</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.cec.yamanashi.ac.jp/~ring/japan/\">Proceedings of the 37th Symposium on Ring Theory and Representation Theory</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Osaka\">Osaka</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://hardy.uhasselt.be/personal/vdbergh/Publications/zdinfty.pdf\">pdf</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Michel Van den Bergh</a> (<b>2007</b>). <i>On global deformation quantization in the algebraic case</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Journal_of_Algebra\">Journal of Algebra</a>, Vol. 315, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://hardy.uhasselt.be/personal/vdbergh/Publications/algebraic_quantization.pdf\">pdf</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Michel Van den Bergh</a> (<b>2008</b>). <i>Double Poisson algebras</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Transactions_of_the_American_Mathematical_Society\">Transactions of the American Mathematical Society</a>, Vol.360, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://hardy.uhasselt.be/personal/vdbergh/Publications/double_poisson.pdf\">pdf</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-11\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Michel Van den Bergh</a> (<b>2009</b>). <i>The Kontsevich weight of a wheel with spokes pointing outward</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://link.springer.com/journal/10468\">Algebras and Representation Theory</a>, Vol. 12 <sup id=\"cite_ref-12\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2010_...\">2010 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Michel_Van_den_Bergh&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: 2010 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Michel Van den Bergh</a> (<b>2010</b>). <i>Notes on formal deformations of abelian categories</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1002.0259\">arXiv:1002.0259</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Michel Van den Bergh</a> (<b>2011</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://arxiv.org/abs/0807.3753\">Noncommutative quadrics</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_Mathematics_Research_Notices\">International Mathematics Research Notices IMRN</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-13\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Michel Van den Bergh</a> (<b>2013</b>). <i>On Involutivity of p-Support</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://xxx.lanl.gov/abs/1309.6677\">arXiv:1309.6677</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-14\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-14\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup> <sup id=\"cite_ref-15\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-15\">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Michel Van den Bergh</a> (<b>2014</b>). <i>Calabi-Yau algebras and superpotentials</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1008.0599\">arXiv:1008.0599v3</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-16\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-16\">&#91;16&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Mathematician#SSpenko\" title=\"Mathematician\">Špela Špenko</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Michel Van den Bergh</a> (<b>2015</b>). <i>Non-commutative resolutions of quotient singularities</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1502.05240\">arXiv:1502.05240</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Mathematician#SSpenko\" title=\"Mathematician\">Špela Špenko</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Michel Van den Bergh</a> (<b>2015</b>). <i>Comparing the commutative and non-commutative resolutions for determinantal varieties of skew symmetric and symmetric matrices</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1511.07290\">arXiv:1511.07290</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Mathematician#SSpenko\" title=\"Mathematician\">Špela Špenko</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Michel Van den Bergh</a> (<b>2016</b>). <i>Semi-orthogonal decompositions of GIT quotient stacks</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1603.02858\">arXiv:1603.02858</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Mathematician#SSpenko\" title=\"Mathematician\">Špela Špenko</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Michel Van den Bergh</a> (<b>2017</b>). <i>Non-commutative crepant resolutions for some toric singularities I</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1701.05255\">arXiv:1701.05255</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-17\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-17\">&#91;17&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Mathematician#SSpenko\" title=\"Mathematician\">Špela Špenko</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Michel Van den Bergh</a> (<b>2017</b>). <i>Non-commutative crepant resolutions for some toric singularities II</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1707.08245\">arXiv:1707.08245</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Michel Van den Bergh</a> (<b>2017</b>). <i>A Practical Introduction to the GSPRT</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://hardy.uhasselt.be/Toga/GSPRT_approximation.pdf\">pdf</a>&#160;» <a href=\"/Match_Statistics#SPRT\" title=\"Match Statistics\">SPRT</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-18\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-18\">&#91;18&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Mathematician#SSpenko\" title=\"Mathematician\">Špela Špenko</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Michel Van den Bergh</a> (<b>2019</b>). <i>A class of perverse schobers in Geometric Invariant Theory</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1908.04213\">arXiv:1908.04213</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-19\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-19\">&#91;19&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Michel Van den Bergh</a> (<b>2019</b>). <i>The Generalized Maximum Likelihood Ratio for the Expectation Value of a Distribution</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://hardy.uhasselt.be/Fishtest/support_MLE_multinomial.pdf\">pdf</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Forum_Posts\">Forum Posts</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Michel_Van_den_Bergh&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" title=\"Edit section: Forum Posts\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2008_...\">2008 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Michel_Van_den_Bergh&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" title=\"Edit section: 2008 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=24108\">Linux port of newer versions of TogaII</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Michel Van den Bergh</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, October 01, 2008</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofo